places.perex: This mountain overlooking the town offers splendid panoramic views. You can imagine how the people watched the Ocean and coming ships.

places.perex: Stop by to sit down to watch one of the Hollywood blockbusters here. More into African films?

places.name: Analakely Market
places.perex: Come to this seductive market where you’ll find locals haggling for clothing and produce. A lot of prey to be found here!

places.perex: This fairy-tale colourful-icing like building is a judicial court. But more than admiring its function, see the architectural style!

places.perex: This island is magnetic! Truly, a God's place! Remarkable nature and tranquility.

places.perex: Go for an adrenaline-rushing experience! Scuba-dive and  discover the marvellous undersea life of Nosy Be.

places.name: Mantasoa Reservoir
places.perex: Mantasoa Dam is a buttress dam on the Varahina-North River, a tributary of the Ikopa River, near Mantasoa in the Analamanga Region of…

places.name: Daily Flower Market
places.perex: Shop for fresh cut flowers, extraordinary seeds or unique plants. Or just wander about in this colourful oasis.

places.name: Orca Sakatia Spearfishing & Freediving Centre
places.perex: Something you have never seen and experienced is waiting here for you to be discovered! Incredible fishing and diving with mammoth fish!

places.name: La Medina Day Spa
places.perex: This celestial spa is a sanctuary for the soul. Be it tired, stressed out, here you will regain your confidence after connecting with your…

places.name: Nahampoana Reserve
places.perex: White and black zebra-tailed cutie pie alias lemur is a mascot of this reserve. Admire this beauty along with other species.

places.name: Ranch Solaris
places.perex: This ranch breeding horses offers unique and moving horse promenades and treks across the Malagasy nature.

places.name: Nosy Nato
places.perex: This paradise has not yet been fully discovered by tourist agencies. Its clear blue waters washing the white beaches are celestial.

places.name: Andasibe
places.perex: Tiny town in the middle of nowhere is a tourist-temptation. Why?

places.name: Old Cemetery
places.perex: If you or your kids are passionate about pirates, then you mustn't miss this place where you will find many of their graves.

places.name: Tulear (Toliara)
places.perex: The city with the clearest white sky in the world. Quite a difference to Red Tana.

places.name: Ambatoloaka
places.perex: Those visiting Nosy-Be will most probably not miss this touristy destination. The clear blue sky and sandy beaches make it a must-be-there.

places.name: Pirates Museum Antananarivo
places.perex: Unshowy museum will reveal its secrets and treasures about the piracy history of Madagascar. Find out about Jack Sparrow!

places.name: Mahamasina Sports Palace
places.perex: Head straight to this sports complex if your body needs a body-attack. Whether you work out a lot or not, you will feel great after exercise!

places.name: Bureau du Parc National de L'Isalo
Réserve spéciale du Cap Sainte Marie
Libanona Beach
places.perex: Located in a beautiful bay, its clear blue shallow waters attract locals as well as tourists. Magnificent!

places.name: Square of Andohalo
places.perex: This square is surrounded by a Catholic cathedral, an Andohalo temple and an Anglican cathedral. It's shadowed by tall verdant trees.

places.name: Bookstore Ambohijatovo
places.perex: This neat and popular bookstore will stock you with a pile of books in different genres - African and French literature mostly.

places.name: Manambato
places.perex: This unshowy distinctive village is a tranquil haven. Bathe in the lake, hike in the forests and explore the surroundings.

places.name: Plongee Toukoul
places.perex: To dive is like to emerge in a totally strange but fascinating world. Cornucopia of colours, different shapes and structures!

places.name: Vato Sarilambo
places.perex: This goluptious sculpture of a boar is encompassed by myths. Was it Indians or Arabs who cut it?

places.name: Port Quartier
places.perex: This splendid ravishing quarter is filled with markets, shops, restaurants. There is significant Arabic influence.

places.name: Pandora Nightclub
places.perex: Hot bodies dancing in the rhythm of African and French music. Opening times that should leave you ready for breakfast!

places.name: Ampefy
places.perex: If you are interested in rural areas of Madagascar, then pay a visit to this village. Ask for the path leading to Analavory Geyser.

places.name: Hell-Ville
places.perex: Hell-Ville is nothing to do with hell, it was just named after Anne Chrétien Louis de Hell. It is a quiet sea-side colonial town.

places.name: Saint Laurent Anglican Cathedral
places.perex: In the Malagasy history, the Protestants and Catholics always fought against each other.

places.name: Hotel de Thermes
places.perex: Antsirabe is reputed for its hot springs. In this hotel you can enjoy the tempting baths, relaxing massages and cooling swimming pool.

places.name: Midongy du Sud National Park
places.perex: Little discovered park is home to the second largest rainforest on the island. It's a cool and humid.

places.name: Lake Ampitabe
places.perex: This truly noteworthy natural reserve around the lake is home to various lemurs, amphibians and crocodiles. There's plentiful of palm trees.

places.name: New Mosque
places.perex: The Indo-Pakistani community is of great importance and this mosque is a feature of diversity of the people in Tôlanaro.

places.name: Salary Bay
places.perex: Enchanting beaches, fabulous sea, bewitching nature all around. Hard to reach, but definitely worth it!

places.name: Regional Museum of University of Toamasina
places.perex: The museum covers incredibly many topics from fishing, archaeology, language preservation and conservation projects. Interesting!

places.name: Le Six Disco
places.perex: Down it and dance! This exclusive club is great for a friends hangout! Swing and shake and groove!

places.name: Ambohijatovo Garden
places.perex: Forget about the hustle and bustle of the city and come to this cozy park/garden to refresh yourself.

places.name: Bar Mojo
places.perex: Beer in your hand, tapping in the rhythm and listening to live music? Possible here!

places.name: Monument to the Dead French
places.perex: When you enter the city, you will see a colonial building which commemorates the death of French soldiers defeated by Malagasi army.

places.name: Avenue de l´Indépendence
places.perex: This major mainstream shopping street is linked with various boutiques, shops, offices and restaurants. Nice for an afternoon!

places.name: Museum of Art and Archaeology
places.perex: Exhibits of this museum focus solely on the archaeology, history and culture of Madagascar. They are worth casting an eye on.

places.name: Zahamena National Park
places.perex: This park is a must-see for every nature-lover and those who want to see a concentrated number of species in one place!

places.name: Jazz Club La Residence
places.perex: This is a place to seek out live music! But only on Fridays! Eat, drink and listen.

places.name: Le Palladium
places.perex: Used to be known as Buddha Club, this eclectic and exclusive bar is hard to beat! Standards tend to be high!

places.name: Place de l'Indépendance
places.perex: This verdant garden with diverse multi-coloured flower beds is a nice spot for a little break while sightseeing.

places.name: Boulevard Ratsimilaho
places.perex: This dramatic promenade is very romantic at sunset when couples in love stroll and stop by in the Jardin d'amour. Also good for a jog!

places.name: Is'Art Galerie
places.perex: Hard to miss when this gimmicky gallery has so zany and succulent expositions. A total pick-me-up from a daily routine!

places.name: Fort Flacourt
places.perex: There is relatively little remaining of the colonial fort but a few cannons. The fort is under a restoration and will be accessible soon.

places.name: Temple of Ambohipotsy
places.perex: Nip across the road to this church built by the British architect William Pool in 1863. On its ground Malagasy Christians were killed.

places.name: Ambodifotatra
places.perex: The long main street running out from the port overflows with diverse shops. If you are preparing for a trip, this is where you can equip.

places.name: Réserve spéciale du Cap Sainte Marie
